<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="variation">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Variation.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">RMNH Coel. 41900, UMUTZ-CnidG-28 (Fig. 1d), UMUTZ-CnidG-30, UMUTZ-CnidG-33, RMNH Coel. 41900 and BMNH 1921.10.26.24-2 are yellow with yellow sclerites; UMUTZ-CnidG-21, UMUTZ-CnidG-101 and UMUTZ-CnidG-232 are orange colonies; UMUTZ-CnidG-29 is red. RMNH Coel. 41901 is orange with red polyps (Fig. 1b), polyp sclerites pink, all others yellow. The sclerites of RMNH Coel. 41901 are similar to the holotype (Figs 4, 5) but it has somewhat longer coenenchymal spindles, up to 0.25 mm long (Fig. 5d).</paragraph>
